{/* */} ABOUT ME
“Don’t let your happiness depend on something you may lose.”
-C.S. Lewis

WHO AM I?

I am a 3rd year student studying at the{" "} University of Virginia , majoring in Computer Science & Statistics in the School of Engineering. Currently, I am a SDE Intern at  Volkswagen Credit , a financial branch of the  Volkswagen Group  based in Herndon VA based in the Washington D.C metro area.

Down the road, I aspire to become a full-stack engineer and enjoy challenging myself to learn and use new modern technologies and tools that software development is revolving around today. I am currently in search for a challenging software engineering internship for Summer 2020.

Outside of academics, I enjoy hanging out with friends in my fellowship, playing tennis, and sometimes reading interesting books. I have recently started learning guitar as well.
